premise_source_doc_sentence: The story tells of a group of samurai who were left leaderless  (  becoming rōnin  )  after their daimyō  (  feudal lord  )  Asano Naganori was compelled to commit seppuku  (  ritual suicide  )  for assaulting a court official named Kira Yoshinaka , whose title was Kōzuke no suke .

Seppuku  (  切腹 , `` cutting -LSB- the -RSB- abdomen/belly '' , formal on reading of original Kanji  )  , sometimes metathesized as harakiri  (  腹切り , `` abdomen/belly cutting ''  )  which is a native Japanese kun reading , is a form of Japanese ritual suicide by disembowelment .
